&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;About the NEAR Foundation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://near.org/blog/what-the-near-foundation-does/&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;NEAR Foundation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; is a nonprofit, non-beneficiary foundation based in Switzerland which supports community-driven innovation and the Open Web with a specific focus on the NEAR platform. The Foundation distributes grant funding into the NEAR ecosystem, coordinates governance among participants, educates people about the protocol and ensures that relationships among the community members are as strong and sustainable as the apps they build. It seeks to combine the inclusive care of a community-driven NGO with the at-scale effectiveness of a Silicon Valley startup.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;<p><figure><iframe style="width: 500px; height: 281px;" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/-hOWM-o7N5k" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></figure></p>

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;CoinDesk is seeking a community manager to nurture and grow the community around its social reward token and supporting platforms as a brand ambassador.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;With creating a delightful user experience as their mission, the community manager works closely with audience development, events, product and marketing to build whole spaces from the ground up for fans, including readers, social media followers and event attendees, to interact and develop long-term loyalty and engagement. They communicate between the brand and users with humor, professionalism and authenticity while seizing constantly evolving internet trends.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The CM plays a key role at Consensus 2022, CoinDesk’s first high-profile in-person event in the COVID era, to be based in Austin, Texas, June 9-12. The CM will nurture the Consensus Community virtually and in person, contributing and implementing creative ideas to incentivize attendance, participation and loyalty beyond the event. They will utilize communications channels like Twitter, Discord, Telegram and Reddit, plan and host in-person community events, and manage allocation of $DESK, CoinDesk’s own social token designed to fuel engagement and loyalty, and the rewards in DESK’s NFT store and beyond.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;As a brand voice and key communications innovator for a news and events company, the CM should be very familiar with token-based community models, event management and editorial and journalistic standards. They should be able to leverage the opportunity of sourcing CoinDesk’s deep data and knowledge bases to inform and delight users.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The CM is familiar with metric goals, and enjoys the challenge of developing strategies to meet key performance indicators (KPIs) such as engagement rate, content reach, community growth (organic vs paid), reduction of bounce rate (hand in hand with CTA) and conversion.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
