&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Ripple is hiring an experienced Vice President of Product Finance. This new role will provide a “bridge” between the finance team and product/engineering group as Ripple develops new payment products and scales for growth.&amp;nbsp; You understand the product and technology and have an opinion about what the implementation will look like. This leader will need to be “hands on” in owning all of the details of implementation, while also able to think strategically to identify and prioritize opportunities as well as build out and oversee a team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Reporting to the Ripple CFO, you will partner closely with finance, product and engineering to design and implement our crypto and fiat payment solutions.&amp;nbsp; You will prioritize business needs, define requirements with input from the finance team, and translate those requirements for implementation by our engineering team. You will apply best practices in project management, finance process improvement, and technology implementation (both homegrown and 3rd party) across all of finance. Additionally, you will understand the external finance vendor landscape, understanding product offerings and key points of integration with banks, exchanges and software providers. You will be responsible for building out a team to support the needs of finance and the business.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Partner with product leaders on new initiatives to understand objectives, customer experience, and work together to identify integrations/points of overlap with finance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Lead the finance team in requirements definition by having a deep and clear understanding of the technology, then translate the finance team’s needs into scalable and cost-effective workflows.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Partner across finance (Tax, Treasury, Revenue Operations, Reporting, FP&amp;amp;A, etc) to ensure new products and enhancements are integrated in a timely and consistent way.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Identify inefficiencies in current systems and processes within finance; recommend and implement solutions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Manage key stakeholders to escalate potential risks/issues and assist in development and implementation of mitigation strategies.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Understand vendor landscape as it relates to current and future systems and integrations (e.g., Sage/Intacct, Coupa, partner banks, crypto exchanges, etc.), building relationships with 3rd parties and advising on architecture of the overall system.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Over time, build a team to support product expansion and project management needs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
