&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It’s important to have team members that care about the team’s results more than their own individual achievements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It’s important for leadership to be tolerant of making mistakes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It’s important that the team members help, teach, and mentor one another&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It’s important not to place blame on individuals when things go bad but instead to evaluate as a team how we do it better the next time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It’s important to be clear on what that mission is and minimize the distractions on the teams executing on that mission&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Small teams execute better than big ones, empower small teams with ownership and minimize the dependencies between them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It’s important to encourage self-directed innovation&lt;/li&gt;
