&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agree to Disagree &amp;amp; Commit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; -Voice concerns in a respectful &amp;amp; appropriate manner directly to your manager or the Senior Leadership Team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assume Positive Intent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; - Always start from the idea that a person meant well or was doing their best, no matter what they say or do.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accomplish More with Less&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; - Explore options to maximize value. Learn and be curious.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hold Yourself and Others to High Standards&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; - Embrace high attention to detail &amp;amp; maintain an appropriate sense of urgency.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Speak Up&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; - Everyone’s opinion matters. Be inquisitive &amp;amp; don’t think in silos.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
